The man was part of a group of people demonstrating over what they say is government&#8217;s failure to help those affected by floods. JOHANNESBURG A Boksburg resident has died during a service delivery protest after being hit by a truck.The man was part of a group of people, demonstrating over what they say is government s failure to help those affected by the heavy downpours which damaged houses in Ekhurleni on Monday.Mayor Mzwandile Masina has expressed his sadness over the man s death.Spokesperson Zweli Dlamini says: The mayor has voiced his lamentation around losing a life in what is supposed to be a service delivery protest. The city says food, blankets and alternative accommodation will be provided for those who have been affected by the heavy rains.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)